[[ja:岡山県護国神社]]
'''Okayama Prefecture Gokoku Shrine''' (岡山護国神社) is a {{ill|Gokoku Shrine|ja|護国神社}} located in Okuichi, {{ill|Naka-ku|ja|中区 (岡山市)}}, {{ill|Okayama|ja|岡山市}}, {{ill|Okayama Prefecture|ja|岡山県}}. The former [[Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines]] classification was a Designated Gokoku Shrine by the Minister of Home Affairs, and it became a {{ill|Beppyo shrine|ja|別表神社}} after the war.
[[Ja:岡山護国神社]]
The shrine grounds feature numerous memorial monuments to the war dead, including memorials for those interned in Siberia and a memorial for Navy Vice Admiral {{ill|Matome Ugaki|ja|宇垣纒}} and the seventeen warriors of Kikusui.

== History ==
{{ill|Ikeda Noriyuki|ja|池田章政}}, the lord of {{ill|Okayama Domain|ja|岡山藩}}, held a spirit summoning festival for 34 war dead, including {{ill|Suzume Hachiro Tokioki|ja|雀部八郎時宜}} from the {{ill|Boshin War|ja|戊辰戦争}}'s {{ill|Battle of Aizu|ja|奥羽戦争}}, on April 3, {{ill|1869|ja|1869th year}} ({{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 2), at the current site of {{ill|Korakuen|ja|後楽園}} park's back bamboo field. In June of the same year, a shrine and stone monument were built on an 180 tsubo site in Kamida Village, Joto District, to worship the war dead from the Aizu and {{ill|Hakodate War|ja|函館戦争}}.

On March 17, [[:en:1874|1874]] (Meiji 7), it became an official government shrine and was named Okayama Shokonsha. In [[:en:1922|1922]] (Taisho 4), it was relocated to its current location, and the shrine buildings were completed on April 26. On April 1, {{ill|1939|ja|1939th year}} (Showa 14), it was designated by the Minister of Home Affairs and renamed Okayama Prefecture Gokoku Shrine. For a period after the war, it was called Sōzan Shrine due to the Allied occupation policies, but it reverted to its current name in {{ill|1952|ja|1952nd year |lt=1955}} (Showa 27). Various renovations have been carried out since the war.

== Access ==
* {{ill|Okayama Prefectural Route 28 Okayama Ushimado Line|ja|岡山県道28号岡山牛窓線}}
* Take the {{ill|Ryobi Bus|ja|両備ホールディングス}} bound for {{ill|Saidaiji Bus Center|ja|西大寺バスセンター}} and get off at "Gokoku Shrine" bus stop.

