'''Okayama Prefecture Gokoku Shrine''' (岡山護国神社) is a {{ill|Gokoku Shrine|ja|護国神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in Okuichi, {{ill|Naka-ku|ja|中区 (岡山市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Okayama|ja|岡山市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Okayama Prefecture|ja|岡山県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The former [[Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines]] classification was a Designated Gokoku Shrine by the Minister of Home Affairs, and it became a {{ill|Beppyo shrine|ja|別表神社|1=Beppyo Shrine|2=ja|3=別表神社|4=simple|5=Beppyo shrine|6=zh|7=別表神社|8=mr|9=बेप्प्यो तीर्थ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} after the war.
[[Ja:岡山護国神社]]
The shrine grounds feature numerous memorial monuments to the war dead, including memorials for those interned in Siberia and a memorial for Navy Vice Admiral {{ill|Matome Ugaki|ja|宇垣纒|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the seventeen warriors of Kikusui.

